{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54266a10-c1fb-47dd-a4a5-9b9ffcac6386","content":"I don't see any `.dmp` file in the current directory. To help you analyze it, I'll need a couple of things:\n\n1. **Where is the dump file?** Please provide the full path to the `.dmp` file, or copy/move it into the current directory.\n2. **What runtime?** Is this a .NET Framework app or .NET Core / .NET 5+? This determines which tools to use (e.g., `dotnet-dump`, `windbg`, `lldb` + SOS).\n\nIn the meantime — on Linux, the typical approach is:\n\n```bash\n# Install the diagnostic tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-file.dmp>\n```\n\nOnce inside, useful commands include:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` (print exception) — last exception details\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\nLet me know the file location and I'll dig in!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b8926d26-00b0-4362-a1e7-65a3aec1a6ac","outputTokens":247,"requestId":"7654:2D596F:E540C0:10D3779:69FE93AA"},"id":"c7578114-f1ce-460e-b050-ba1c65f3368a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:53:53.095Z","parentId":"349ab9a5-370d-407b-b61c-0dd2958f1eb3"}
